WEBVTT

00:04:58.267 --> 00:05:00.093
that officers need to understand

00:05:00.117 --> 00:05:02.935
the history and the power
of their uniforms.

00:05:03.458 --> 00:05:06.276
They're going to have to set aside
old historical narratives

00:05:06.290 --> 00:05:07.855
that do not serve them well.

00:05:08.220 --> 00:05:10.878
And that means they have to learn
about implicit bias.

00:05:11.204 --> 00:05:14.142
Implicit biases are shortcuts
the brain makes

00:05:14.166 --> 00:05:15.903
without us really knowing it.

00:05:15.927 --> 00:05:19.767
They're stereotypes
that often influence our decision making.

00:05:20.434 --> 00:05:21.671
And so, you can imagine,

00:05:21.695 --> 00:05:25.061
for police officers who have to make
split-second decisions

00:05:25.085 --> 00:05:28.352
can be a very detrimental
decision-making point.

